 MT goes down unplanned and the aggro is free until second MT gains it does this work, is it a good idea?<br><br>First MT goes down and shout in zone is MT down sk blank burn aggro.<br><br>sk blank then fires DT and does everything possible to gain aggro, there by keeping mob on sk.  <br><br>Sk is not healed and dies inorder to give second MT time to build aggro up to take aggro when sk is dead.<br><br>&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;----- Any idea if that does work or would work? <br><br>On a side note how do our warrior brothers who are 2nd MT manage to stay under aggro durring combat and yet grab it the fastest after 1st MT is down?  <br><br>Trying to compare notes with what my guild currently uses as tactics.  <br><br>Would love any solid feedback you great paladins can give me.<br><br>Thanks<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uazzigothghul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azzigoth Ghul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 6:34:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback on the LoH on raids and other high end paladin </span><hr size=1> - Have you even experienced any of your scenario's?<br><br><br>Which mobs do you LoH MT before the clerics begin CH chain? <br>- LoH is emergency buffer if the CH chain lags.  I've used it in the beginning, midway, and to help in a MT switch.<br><br><br>If LoH isn't a full heal yet do you put two palies on it?<br>- LoH is 2520.  Most MT's are 6k+.  So it's about 1/3 heal and only succeeds in buying time for a cleric CH.<br><br>What hot keys you use during this?<br>- /target MT, /assist MT, LoH<br><br>Do you save other paladins' LoH for the second MT?<br>- Try to communicate with other paladins who has LoH up.<br>You can setup a fixed LoH order, but we tend to know when to trigger it.  Unspoken order.  Bottom line is to watch MT health, and if it drops to 2 bubbs, you fire LoH.  <br><br>MT switches can be risky.  It's better to overheal and keep aggro on MT with CH chain targeted than have the mob ping pong after a bad MT switch.<br><br><br>When the MT goes down unplanned and the aggro is free until second MT gains it does this work, is it a good idea?<br>- SK's are a bit of a rarity.  We have 8 warriors.  Typically if the MT falls, another warrior will step in.<br>To help the aggro control, tanks are to stop attacking immediately when MT falls, and wait until the ST calls them in.<br>Tanks who can not control their aggro, are SEVERELY dealt with.  ie. TL out, removed from raid.<br><br>On a side note how do our warrior brothers who are 2nd MT manage to stay under aggro durring combat and yet grab it the fastest after 1st MT is down? <br>- A lot of aggro is proximity.  Assuming the warrior is doing decent dmg during the fight, and all tanks stop attacking from max melee range.  The warrior should be able to get aggro.<br>There are a lot of key weapons that warriors use to get aggro fast.<br><br>Probably the best mob to learn big mob tactics is Vind.<br>He has decent HP, and high enough dmg output to need CH chain.  He can also be slowed allowing room for some mistakes.<br>Some start with Velk, but I consider Vind to be the first cherry popper.  When we started we would use an MT and ST with large numbers.<br>As time went on we use a lot less people and the MT lives the entire fight.<br><br>Practice makes perfect. <p><BR><B><FONT SIZE="1" face="Verdana"><B><FONT SIZE="2" face="Verdana">Azzigoth</a><BR><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath"><B><FONT SIZE="1" face="Verdana"> Crusader</a> -<a href="http://www.fallenlegacy.com/"><B><FONT SIZE="1" face="Verdana"> Fallen Legacy</a> -<a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum"><B><FONT SIZE="1" face="Verdana"> Lanys T'vyl</a> <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39056" target="_blank"><B><FONT SIZE="1" face="Verdana"> My Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubeldukil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beldukil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 3622<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 6:56:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://beld.freeservers.com/images/beld.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback on the LoH on raids and other high end paladin </span><hr size=1> As far as I know Vindi cant be slowed, unless this is a recent change. <p><center><imgsrc="http://beld.freeservers.com/images/beld.jpg"> <br><table border=0>  <tr><td><imgsrc="http://www.wise.k12.va.us/cms/images/animatedKnightLeft.gif">    </td><td>Beldukil Lawbringer<br> Level 60 Crusader of Tunare<br>Innit<br>Xev<br>    </td><td><img src="http://www.wise.k12.va.us/cms/images/animatedKnightLeft.gif"></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujeet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeet</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 11:36:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback on the LoH on raids and other high end paladin </span><hr size=1> The only time I use LH on a MT is <br><br>1) early if the cleric chain needs some help at the start or <br><br>2) to get on the rampage list and tank rampages.<br><br>On the tank switching...just give your first tank a smidgen of time to get agro (he should have decent taunting weapons to keep it as well).    Barring extraordinary circumstances, that first MT should hold agro till he dies, and then your 2nd MT (if he also has decent taunting weapons) should pick up agro shortly after.   A couple people may have to /attack off and such, but your 2nd MT if properly equipped shouldn't have a problem picking up agro.<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujeet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeet</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/14/02 11:37:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udisavowedknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Disavowed Knight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/15/02 5:21:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback on the LoH on raids and other high end paladin </span><hr size=1> Thanks for the feedback.  <br><br>Some guilds have posted that some mobs the paladin LoH is used to keep clerics from gaining aggro when the ch chain first starts.  Has anyone here heard/done this?  If so what mobs? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaauan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aauan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/17/02 11:41:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback on the LoH on raids and other high end paladin </span><hr size=1> i posted a question about the LoH rotation awhile back and got some good feedback. some mobs have insane heal agro and LoH rotation is handy in these situtations.<br><br>pally's dropping LoH then casting Da immediately after should give the MA plenty of time to establish agro without clerics pulling it off with Cheals.<br><br>i'm sure my posts is still on this board somewhere, check it out it's a good read.<br><br><br>---Ariakkas <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52762 </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 288<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 5:19:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback on the LoH on raids and other high end paladin </span><hr size=1> &quot;Which mobs do you LoH MT before the clerics begin CH chain? &quot;<br><br>I do not really plan a lay hand before a CH chain for particular mobs. But I do &quot;guard&quot; the MT the first 15 second of a fight and only engage after the CH chain seems to be flowly smootly. <br><br>This is particular important if the distance to charge a mob is far and clerics need to get to a guarded spot to heal.  <br><br>&quot;If LoH isn't a full heal yet do you put two palies on it?&quot;<br><br>Lay hand at 60 is 2520 or so heal. Typically complete heal is most likely 3.5-4k. So the lay hand is not too far behind the typical CH.<br><br>Most chains are somewhere at 5-8 seconds so hopefully your clerics get their rhythm going in 5 seconds again =p<br><br>&quot;What hot keys you use durring this?&quot;<br><br>I used to use a full macro for lay hand (/doability) and ooc. A few times this macro failed for no obvious reasons so I switch back to manual lay hands and a hotkey to ooc it. (That way you can also hide better if you wasted your lay hand on the mob =p)<br><br>&quot;Do you save other paladins' LoH for the second MT?&quot;<br><br>Lay hands are really not that planned out. If you play a good paladin you watch the &quot;goes beserk&quot; messages and death of MT messages. On the beserk message I slam assist quick and watch if CH comes in. Should the HPs drop fast then I lay hand at 1 bubb regardless.<br><br>When I see the MT death message I slam assist again and scan for a viable second MT. If the player that has aggro is not a good MT (sorry chanters and rangers) then I double tap assist for next player. When I stop at a warrior I watch his health and lay hands at 2 bubbs to give clerics a chance to shift CH chain.<br><br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=41.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm